# Kimi / Moonshot Provider Rules

Docs: https://platform.kimi.ai/ · https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/llms.txt  
Base URL default: `https://api.moonshot.ai/v1` — see `internal/config/urls.go`
(override: `DISCURSIVE_MOONSHOT_BASE_URL`).

## Supported models (MVP)

| API model ID | Role |
| ---- | --- |
| `kimi-k3` | Default flagship; 1M context; always thinks |
| `kimi-k2.6` | Image-capable coding model; both thinking modes |

## Per-model parameter matrix (do not cross-apply)

| Concern | `kimi-k3` | `kimi-k2.6` |
| ---- | --- | --- |
| Thinking | Top-level `reasoning_effort` (`"max"` only today). **Do not** send K2 `thinking` | Use K2 `thinking` object when needed; **do not** send `reasoning_effort` |
| Sampling | Many fields fixed — **omit** temperature/top_p/penalties/n | Follow model reference; strip Cursor-only junk |
| Tool loops | Return **complete** assistant message incl. `reasoning_content` | Preserve tool_call pairing; reasoning placeholder rules per gateway |
| Streaming | Separate `reasoning_content` vs `content` deltas | Same OpenAI-compat SSE family |

Official docs: [K3 quickstart](https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/guide/kimi-k3-quickstart),
[Model parameter reference](https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/api/models-overview).

## Out of MVP (document only)

- Moonshot Formula official tools (`/tools` + `/fibers`) — Cursor already supplies
  MCP/tools; not a transparent proxy feature. Web-search currently discouraged
  by platform near-term.
- Batch API, Playground, MoonPalace — ops/debug, not the Cursor gateway path.

**Cross-provider:** DeepSeek models and thinking live in `deepseek.mdc`. The
gateway model map (`gateway.mdc`) routes aliases to Moonshot **or** DeepSeek —
do not hardcode Moonshot-only assumptions in shared sanitize code.

### `K3 thinking param mismatch`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Moonshot 400 / unexpected thinking behavior on K3 | Sent K2 `thinking` or omitted required replay of `reasoning_content` | Use `reasoning_effort`; strip `thinking`; replay full assistant messages |

## Kimi Context Caching

- **Fully automatic, content-prefix-hash based.** No API parameters required.
  Cache fires when the request prefix matches a previously-seen prefix within
  the TTL window (5-30 minutes).
- **`prompt_cache_key` is a routing hint, NOT cache control.** It increases
  the probability of keeping related requests on the same cluster (where warm
  KV cache lives), but does not create, bind, or partition caches. Kimi's
  `kimi-cli` uses it for this purpose.
- **First request to Kimi in a session is always cold.** Cache hits begin on
  request 2+ when the prefix matches. Switching providers mid-session resets
  cache state (new prefix, new cluster).
- **256-token chunk alignment** for cached reads. Small prefix changes
  (including `reasoning_content` on non-K3 models) can shift alignment
  boundaries and reduce cacheable tokens.
- **Generation parameters** (`temperature`, `top_p`, `reasoning_effort`) do
  NOT participate in cache identity. Our sanitizer sets `reasoning_effort:
  "max"` for all K3 requests — this is stable and cache-friendly.
- **`cached_tokens`** is the single field Kimi returns for cache hits (unlike
  DeepSeek's `prompt_cache_hit_tokens` / `prompt_cache_miss_tokens`). Our
  `parseUsageObject` derives hit/miss from it.

